          <h1>Methodology</h1>
          <hr></hr>
    <p class="flow-text">Rates for ARMs are determined using a probabilty distribution where the spectrum of possible outcomes begins at 2.5% and peaks at 15%.  The most likely outcomes are between rates of 2.5% & 6%.  Depending on the current rate, the area below/above that rate is determined.  A 1..100 number is randomly generated and subtracted from the area below the incoming rate.  This number is then assumed to be basis points adjustment for that year.  The adjustments are summed if the ARM has adjustment periods of longer than one year.</p>
